    <stitle>STARTING MOTORS - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="3">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <para>Under normal operating conditions, no maintenance will be required between engine overhaul periods. At
            time of engine overhaul, motors should be disassembled, inspected, cleaned, and tested as described in
            succeeding paragraphs.
        </para>
        <para>As shown in the cross sectional views of
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0803604">Figure 4</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0803605">Figure 5</hotlnk>, and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0803606">Figure 6</hotlnk>the nose housing is attached to the lever housing by means of
            bolts located around the outside of the housing. To relocate the housing, it is only necessary to remove the
            bolts, rotate the housing to the desired position, and re-install the bolts.
        </para>
